commit.message:
Release version v1.0.8

Signed-off-by: nevola <laura.garcia@zevenet.com>

zcutils: update zcutils tools

Use http definitions, update log functions, update buffer definitions.

Signed-off-by: nevola <laura.garcia@zevenet.com>

tests: upadte api tests with local farm changes and add new test

Signed-off-by: nevola <laura.garcia@zevenet.com>

nft: fix nat service for local farms

This allows to take advantage of nat stage for local services, such as ct mark
synchronization with skbuff and input logging options.

Signed-off-by: nevola <laura.garcia@zevenet.com>

logs: fix syslog output

After the integration of zcutils, the logging was not working
properly.

Signed-off-by: nevola <laura.garcia@zevenet.com>

tests: fix tests outputs

Signed-off-by: nevola <laura.garcia@zevenet.com>

config: fix parsing error for limit with empty value

We can get the following parsing error with empty or 0 value for limits:

" error parsing buffer. Parsing unknown value '' in 'new-rtlimit' "

Empty or 0 value will disable the limit, if no unit provided then
it will be untouched.

Signed-off-by: nevola <laura.garcia@zevenet.com>

nft: enable prerouting and postrouting chains for local virtual services as well

Currently, only prerouting and postrouting tables are created for local farms,
but some use cases would require these chains in order to control the
conntrack marks, as an example.

Signed-off-by: nevola <laura.garcia@zevenet.com>

zcutils: integrate zevenet core utils

Integration of the zevenet core utils in order to improve maintenance
of the l4 load balancer core (nftlb) and l7 load balancer proxy (zproxy)
common functions.

Signed-off-by: nevola <laura.garcia@zevenet.com>

tests: improve testing platform

The number of tests are increasing and we need a way to
execute grouping tests without executing sequentially
all of them.

New arguments are required:
-g <group name> : directory of tests to be executed
-s <number> : number of test to stop
-r : apply the reports generated in order to update the
     test output

Signed-off-by: nevola <laura.garcia@zevenet.com>

Release version v1.0.7

Signed-off-by: nevola <laura.garcia@zevenet.com>

backends: allow to set _off_ backend after _down_ state

A backend could be set as off from or to a down state, otherwise,
when setting up status to a backend from down and then off, some
the back to the client traffic is not managed properly. A command
error was shown.

Signed-off-by: nevola <laura.garcia@zevenet.com>

server: add NFTLB_SERVER_KEY environment variable to set the key

This way, the key is delivered in a more secure fashion.

Signed-off-by: nevola <laura.garcia@zevenet.com>

Release version v1.0.6

Signed-off-by: nevola <laura.garcia@zevenet.com>

tests: add tests for backends with and without port

Signed-off-by: nevola <laura.garcia@zevenet.com>

backends: fix all backends with ports during backend creation

By default, when creating a new backend there is no port so this
variable should be reset.

Signed-off-by: nevola <laura.garcia@zevenet.com>

tests: update api tests

Signed-off-by: nevola <laura.garcia@zevenet.com>

tests: add api tests for patch and backend ports set and update

Signed-off-by: nevola <laura.garcia@zevenet.com>

backends: apply backends set ip and port when all backend have it

The backends set will configure ip and port if all of them have it.
Before, only one at least one with port will configure ip and port.

Signed-off-by: nevola <laura.garcia@zevenet.com>

policies: enable PATCH verb in order to be able to update a set atomically

The PATCH verb is only used to update at once and atomically a set of
new elements discarding the current content, applying a flush and
creating the new elements.

Signed-off-by: nevola <laura.garcia@zevenet.com>

sessions: delete trivial debug printing

Signed-off-by: nevola <laura.garcia@zevenet.com>

Release version v1.0.5

Signed-off-by: nevola <laura.garcia@zevenet.com>

sessions: introduce support of sessions reload after backend discovery update with expiration

Signed-off-by: nevola <laura.garcia@zevenet.com>

readme: update zevenet knowledge-base url

Signed-off-by: nevola <laura.garcia@zevenet.com>

Release version v1.0.4

Signed-off-by: nevola <laura.garcia@zevenet.com>

tests: update tests with latests changes

Signed-off-by: nevola <laura.garcia@zevenet.com>

nft: fix inclusion of new backend in forward services map

Without this partch, the inclusion of a new backend is not properly
done due to the handling of reload in run_nftst_rules_gen_vsrv().
Force the creation and reload of rules in the farm forwarding chain.

Signed-off-by: nevola <laura.garcia@zevenet.com>
